rComments: Pay attention/participate in lectures and you'll do fine in her class. Do this in addition to completing the assigned readings and you'll probably end up with an A. In regards to group assignments, pretty simple here: stay on-track with your team and you'll do well, leave everything last minute and you'll probably fail.

She is a genuine, nice person however and cares for students to do well. Another good thing is that there's often bonuses to boost your mark.
She's a very good professor, takes the time to give proper feedback and genuinely a very nice person. Would definitely take her again for my class!
